HEADWORD: Diacid
<hw>Di*ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>di-</ets>
+ <ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Divalent; -- said of a
base or radical as capable of saturating two acid monad radicals or a
dibasic acid. Cf. <er>Dibasic</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and
<er>Biacid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

